    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for golang-github-openprinting-ipp-usb.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 10.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "HTTP reverse proxy, backed by IPP-over-USB connection to device. It enables\n driverless support for USB devices capable of using IPP-over-USB protocol.\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* crypto/x509: golang: Go crypto/x509: Denial of Service via inefficient certificate chain validation (CVE-2026-32281)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      },
